{"title":"Bailey J. Anderson","markdown":{"headingText":"Bailey J. Anderson","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"::: {.hero-full}\n![](images/hero.jpg)\n:::\n\n::: {.home-layout}\n\n::: {.home-sidebar}\n\n![](images/portrait.jpg)\n\n::: {.profile-links-vertical}\n\n<a href=\"mailto:bailey.anderson@slf.ch\">\n  <i class=\"bi bi-envelope-fill\"></i>\n  <span>Email</span>\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=40Ppn9IAAAAJ\" target=\"_blank\">\n  <i class=\"bi bi-mortarboard-fill\"></i>\n  <span>Google Scholar</span>\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.slf.ch/en/staff/anderson/\" target=\"_blank\">\n  <i class=\"bi bi-building\"></i>\n  <span>WSL / ETH</span>\n</a>\n\n:::\n\n:::\n\n::: {.home-main}\n\n\n## Hydrologist\n\nI seek to understand why apparently similar catchments respond differently to similar forcings, and how those responses emerge from interacting hydrological processes across space and time.\n\n[Research](research.qmd){.button} [Download CV](cv.qmd){.button}\n\n## Research Themes\n\n::: {.research-grid}\n\n::: {.research-card}\n[![](images/diversity.jpg){alt=\"Hydrological response\"}](research.html#catchment-response-diversity)\n\n::: {.research-card-text}\n### [Hydrological response](research.html#catchment-response-diversity)\n\nWhy do apparently similar catchments respond differently?\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.research-card}\n[![](images/extremes.jpg){alt=\"Variability and whiplash\"}](research.html#variability-and-whiplash)\n\n::: {.research-card-text}\n### [Variability and Whiplash](research.html#variability-and-whiplash)\n\nUnderstanding rapid state changes in streamflow.\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.research-card}\n[![](images/processes.jpg){alt=\"Methodology\"}](research.html#hydrological-processes)\n\n::: {.research-card-text}\n### [Methodology](research.html#hydrological-processes)\n\nChallenging how methodological choices influence scientific conclusions.\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n\n:::\n\n:::","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"